# Required
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# SSL: set to 0 to allow self-signed certificates (e.g. corporate proxy, local dev)
# WARNING: disables TLS verification — do not use in production
NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0

# Optional
PORT=3000

# Phase 2: Trello (uncomment when connecting real API)
# TRELLO_API_KEY=
# TRELLO_TOKEN=

# Phase 2: Asana (uncomment when connecting real API)
# ASANA_TOKEN=

# GitHub Issues integration (real API)
GITHUB_TOKEN=            # Required: PAT with repo/public_repo scope
GITHUB_TRIGGER_LABEL=ai-review  # Label that triggers analysis (default: ai-review)
GITHUB_MENTION=@task-ai         # Mention keyword in comments (default: @task-ai)

# Security audit notes (npm audit 2026-03-09):
#
# ACCEPTED RISK — gray-matter transitive dep on js-yaml@3.x (CVE-2025-64718):
#   gray-matter uses js-yaml only to parse YAML front-matter in config files
#   (.github/task-ai.md) fetched from repos we control. Input is trusted.
#   gray-matter is the chosen library per the approved design; do not replace it.
#   No upstream fix is available without switching libraries.
#
# CANNOT FIX WITHOUT BREAKING CHANGES:
#   - ai <=5.0.51 (GHSA-rwvc-j5jr-mgvh) + jsondiffpatch XSS (GHSA-33vc-wfww-vjfv):
#     fix requires ai@6 (breaking). Tracked for next major upgrade of @mastra/core.
#   - tar <=7.5.9 / fastembed (multiple CVEs): fix requires @mastra/core@1.x (breaking).
#     These affect the ONNX/fastembed code path, not the HTTP server or agent logic.
#   - fast-xml-parser (GHSA-fj3w-jwp8-x2g3): patched by npm audit fix (non-breaking).
